\"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.072108609522604e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 345, \"end\": 362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Team South Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With less than four days to go before the 2024 Paralympics opens in Paris,Team South Africahas arrived and settled in the athletes village, ready to play a full part in the success of the event.\", \"from\": 413, \"to\": 607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 481, \"end\": 486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.072108609522604e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the latest Paris Paralympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section for free-to-read content  For these Games there are a record number of countries competing (168), a record number of para-athletes (4 400), a record number of female athletes (1 983) and a record number of events for females (235).\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 624, \"end\": 629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.072108609522604e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The chef de mission for Team SA,Patience Shikwambana, says that the figures show the necessary growth that females have made within the Paralympic movement.\", \"from\": 939, \"to\": 1095, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 968, \"end\": 970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.797901410705816e-66, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 971, \"end\": 979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patience\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.315093016714721e-19, \"text\": \"Patience\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patience\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patience\"}, {\"begin\": 1075, \"end\": 1094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympic movement\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If you consider that at the Sydney 2000 Paralympics there were 988 female athletes and that number has doubled to what it is in 2024 it highlights the way the Games have moved forward.\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1282, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1126, \"end\": 1149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sydney 2000 Paralympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Paralympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We as Team SA are excited to play a significant role in the success of the Games and are excited to start\\u00a0our campaign on Wednesday.\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1415, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1294, \"end\": 1296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.797901410705816e-66, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Everything is in place for a successful Games.\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1462, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the last Paralympics in Tokyo, Team SA achieved seven medals, four of which were gold.\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1553, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1491, \"end\": 1496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9335270096586078, \"rank\": 0.07120628503895768, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1503, \"end\": 1505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.797901410705816e-66, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two of those gold medals came from Ntando Mahlangu who is not in Paris this time around, while a third gold medallist from Tokyo, Anrune Weyers, has retired.\", \"from\": 1554, \"to\": 1711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1589, \"end\": 1604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ntando_Mahlangu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ntando Mahlangu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ntando_Mahlangu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ntando_Mahlangu\"}, {\"begin\": 1619, \"end\": 1624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.072108609522604e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1677, \"end\": 1682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9335270096586078, \"rank\": 0.07120628503895768, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1684, \"end\": 1697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anrune_Weyers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anrune Weyers\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anrune_Weyers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anrune_Weyers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the fourth gold medallist, Pieter du Preez, is back in the hand-cycling event.\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1748, \"end\": 1763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pieter_du_Preez\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pieter du Preez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pieter_du_Preez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pieter_du_Preez\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Flag-bearers for Team SA at Wednesday's opening ceremony are para-athleteMpumelelo Mhlongoand para-swimmerKat Swanepoel.\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1921, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1823, \"end\": 1825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.797901410705816e-66, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both were in Tokyo, although they too will find the atmosphere different considering the last Games were held in a restricted Covid-19 environment.\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 2069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1935, \"end\": 1940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9335270096586078, \"rank\": 0.07120628503895768, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The most experienced members of Team SA are also female.\", \"from\": 2071, \"to\": 2127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2108, \"end\": 2110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.797901410705816e-66, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Equestrian's Philippa Johnson-Dwyer and wheelchair tennis star Kgothatso \\\"KG\\\" Montjane are attending their sixth and fifth such Games' respectively.\", \"from\": 2129, \"to\": 2277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2142, \"end\": 2150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippa_of_Hainault\", \"score\": 0.9999996085981222, \"rank\": 3.896725350317788e-07, \"text\": \"Philippa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippa_of_Hainault\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippa_of_Hainault\"}, {\"begin\": 2203, \"end\": 2205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_the_Garter\", \"score\": 0.999390496650625, \"rank\": 0.000586998458134151, \"text\": \"KG\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_the_Garter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_the_Garter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have a strong blend of experienced and youth in our 2024 squad,\\\" said Shikwambana, who added that the athletes were likely to encounter warm conditions throughout their competition.\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2464, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's still deep in summer here in Paris so hydrating will be of vital importance to our para-athletes,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2501, \"end\": 2506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.072108609522604e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have representation across nine codes and are excited about getting started.\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The financial incentives for medallists are the same as they are for the Paris 2024 Olympic athletes: athletes who win gold will be awarded R400 000, with the coach receiving R100 000.\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2737, \"end\": 2747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999222382, \"rank\": 7.775791857954357e-10, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Silver medallists will earn R200 000 and R50 000, while the bronze medal payouts will be R75 000 and R25 000 for the athlete and coach, respectively.\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 2998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2938, \"end\": 2941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R75_(South_Africa)\", \"score\": 0.9634108711081808, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"R75\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R75_(South_Africa)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R75_(South_Africa)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To recognise the unique nature of the Paralympics,guidesfor visually impaired athletes will also receive the same payouts as the coaches of those athletes that earn a medal.\", \"from\": 3000, \"to\": 3173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For Boccia, where Team SA will be competing, the following incentives will apply:  R200 000 per athlete and R100 000 for the coach for a gold medal  R100 000 per athlete and R50 000 for the coach for a silver medal  R40 000 per athlete and R20 000 for the coach for a bronze medal  The Paris 2024 Paralympics will run from 28 August to 8 September.\", \"from\": 3175, \"to\": 3523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3179, \"end\": 3185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boccia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.297373384196822e-14, \"text\": \"Boccia\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boccia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boccia\"}, {\"begin\": 3198, \"end\": 3200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.797901410705816e-66, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 3461, \"end\": 3471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999222382, \"rank\": 7.775791857954357e-10, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Men: Shaun Anderson (W1)  Management: Barbara Manning  Men: Mpumelelo Mhlongo (T44 100m and long jump), Kerwin Noemdo (F46 shot put), Puseletso Mabote (T63 100m and long jump), Collen Mahlalela (T47 400m), Khumo Pitso (T46 high jump), Jaco Smit (T12 100m), Daniel du Plessis (T62 400m), Hermanus Blom (F12 shot put), Erasmus Badenhorst (guide, 1500m), Claus Kempen (guide, marathon) and Paul Daniels (T22 400m)  Women: Simone Kruger (T38 discus), Sheryl James (T37 100m, 200m, 400m), Louzanne Coetzee (T11 1500m and marathon), Liezel Gouws (T37 400m and long jump), Yane van der Merwe (F44 discus) and Tezna Abrahams (T44 long jump and 200m)  Management: Lappies Swanepoel, Jason Sewanyana, Michael Louwrens and Daniel Damon  BOCCIA  Men: Karabo Cassius Morapedi (BC3) and Matobako Vincent Ramochela (BC3 ramp operator)  Women: Elanza Jordaan (BC3) and Sandre Jordaan (BC3 ramp operator)  Management: Reinet Barnard and Marisa Potgieter  CYCLING  Men: Pieter du Preez  Management: Mark Williams (mechanic) and Ilse du Preez  EQUESTRIAN  Women: Philippa Johnson-Dwyer and Christiaan Haazen (groom)  Manager: Ingeborg Sanne  JUDO  Men: Ndyeni Lamani (J1, under 73kg)  Management: Dirk Crafford  PARA-TRIATHLON  Women: Kirsty Weir  Management: Rohan Kennedy  SWIMMING  Men: Nathan Hendricks (S13 200m individual medley, 100m backstroke, SB13 100m breaststroke) and Christian Sadie (S7 50m butterfly, 100m backstroke, 50m freestyle, SM7 200m individual medley)  Women: Alani Ferreira (S12 400m freestyle, SB12 100m breaststroke, SM12 200m Individual Medley, S12-S13 100m butterfly), Danika Vyncke (SB13 100m breaststroke) and Kat Swanepoel (SM5 200m Individual Medley, S5 50m backstroke, 100m freestyle, 200m freestyle, SB4 100m breaststroke, S14 400m freestyle)  Management: Theo Verster, Chad Peterson and Julayga Cassim  WHEELCHAIR TENNIS  Men: Alwande Sikhosana, Donald Ramphadi and Lucas Sithole  Women: Kgothatso Montjane and Mariska Venter  Management: Genevieve Barnes and Patrick Selepe  Gary Lemkeis reporting live from Paris for the Team SA website for the duration of the Paris Paralympics 2024  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring!\", \"from\": 3525, \"to\": 5708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3530, \"end\": 3544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Anderson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shaun Anderson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Anderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Anderson\"}, {\"begin\": 3959, \"end\": 3962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_T38\", \"score\": 0.9999999991905497, \"rank\": 6.164035307578616e-10, \"text\": \"T38\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_T38\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_T38\"}, {\"begin\": 3972, \"end\": 3984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheryl_James\", \"score\": 0.862068623756732, \"rank\": 0.16000000000000425, \"text\": \"Sheryl James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wi